article.headline: Canisius 71, Youngstown State 59
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Chuck Harris scored 16 points and Ola Matti added 11 to help Canisius to a 71-59 win over Youngstown State on Tuesday night. Darnell Wilson had nine rebounds for the Golden Griffins (2-3), who took a 44-29 lead at halftime and never trailed. Harris was 5-of-10 from the field and made all four of his free throw attempts. Quin Humphrey led Youngstown State (2-5) with 27 points and seven rebounds. He was 9-of-18 shooting, including 5-of-10 from 3-point range, and was 4-of-4 at the foul line. Keston Roberts had 12 points. Canisius scored 31 points on 24 turnovers by the Penguins. Youngstown State shot 48 percent (23-of-48), while the Golden Griffins shot about 43 percent (26-of-61).
